---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Services" description="Farlink Systems provides industrial automation, electrical testing, arc flash studies, and support for government and public infrastructure work.">
  <section class="page-intro">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow">Services</span>
      <h1>Work we do.</h1>
      <p>
        Most jobs fit one service cleanly. Some need a mix. Either way, the goal is the same: clear scope and work that helps
        the site run better.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container service-list">
      <article class="service-block">
        <div class="service-head">
          <span class="kicker">01</span>
          <h2>Industrial automation</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="service-body">
          <p>
            Controls design, PLC programming, HMI work, integration, startup, and troubleshooting for industrial and process
            sites. The focus is not just getting it to run once. It has to be usable by operations and maintainable after handoff.
          </p>

          <ul class="list-reset checklist service-points">
            <li>PLC programming and modifications</li>
            <li>HMI screens and operator workflows</li>
            <li>Controls design and panel support</li>
            <li>System integration and commissioning</li>
            <li>Remote monitoring and industrial networking</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="service-block">
        <div class="service-head">
          <span class="kicker">02</span>
          <h2>Electrical testing and commissioning</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="service-body">
          <p>
            Testing and commissioning work to verify that equipment and systems perform the way they are supposed to. That can be
            part of a new install, or part of finding out why an existing system is not behaving.
          </p>

          <ul class="list-reset checklist service-points">
            <li>Acceptance and proof testing</li>
            <li>Protective device and relay testing</li>
            <li>Power quality checks</li>
            <li>Troubleshooting and corrective support</li>
            <li>Commissioning documentation</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="service-block">
        <div class="service-head">
          <span class="kicker">03</span>
          <h2>Arc flash and power studies</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="service-body">
          <p>
            Arc flash, short circuit, and coordination studies with outputs that are easy to read and act on. The point is to
            help the facility understand risk, labeling, and corrective options without burying the useful part in a pile of fluff.
          </p>

          <ul class="list-reset checklist service-points">
            <li>Arc flash studies</li>
            <li>Short circuit analysis</li>
            <li>Protective device coordination</li>
            <li>Labeling support</li>
            <li>Remediation and next-step guidance</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="service-block">
        <div class="service-head">
          <span class="kicker">04</span>
          <h2>Government, utility, and public infrastructure work</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="service-body">
          <p>
            Support for federal projects, public infrastructure, and water-related work where documentation, compliance, and
            schedule discipline matter. We understand that some jobs need clean paperwork and clean execution at the same time.
          </p>

          <ul class="list-reset checklist service-points">
            <li>Engineering support for government facilities</li>
            <li>Controls and automation for public infrastructure</li>
            <li>Testing, commissioning, and studies</li>
            <li>Water and wastewater system support</li>
            <li>Coordination with owner and contractor teams</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--muted">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="surface callout">
        <span class="eyebrow">Not sure where your project fits?</span>
        <p>
          Send a short note with the site, the problem, and the schedule. We can usually tell you pretty quickly what kind of
          support makes sense.
        </p>
        <div class="button-row">
          <a href="/contact" class="btn">Contact Farlink</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .service-list {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .service-block {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.4rem;
    padding: 1.6rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.62);
    box-shadow: 0 12px 34px rgba(21, 32, 64, 0.05);
  }

  .service-head h2 {
    margin-top: 0.55rem;
  }

  .service-points {
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 860px) {
    .service-block {
      grid-template-columns: minmax(220px, 0.8fr) minmax(0, 1.2fr);
      gap: 2rem;
      align-items: start;
    }
  }
</style>
